Two suspects have been arrested for allegedly shooting dead two people and injuring two others in Giyani in Limpopo Friday night. Police spokesperson, Motlafela Mojapelo says the suspects arrived at a hair salon and one of them produced a firearm. He allegedly shot the salon owner dead, Andrew Makhubele and three other men. Mojapelo says Herman Baloyi who is one of the men who were shot, fled to nearby bushes. Baloyiâ€™s body was recovered this morning after succumbing to gunshot wounds. Other wounded victims were rushed to hospital.